{"name": "torchpwl", "metadata": {"name": "torchpwl", "version": "0.2.0", "classifiers": [], "home_page": "https://github.com/PiotrDabkowski/torchpwl", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["torch"], "summary": "Implementation of Piecewise Linear Functions (PWL) in PyTorch.", "upload_time": 1646519333}, "documentation": ["Piecewise Linear Functions (PWLs) can be used to approximate any 1D function. \nPWLs are built with a configurable number of line segments - the more segments the more accurate the approximation.\nThis package implements PWLs in PyTorch and as such they can be fit to the data using standard gradient descent.\nFor example:\n\nimport torchpwl\n\n# Create a PWL consisting of 3 segments for 5 features - each feature will have its own PWL function.\npwl = torchpwl.PWL(num_features=5, num_breakpoints=3)\nx = torch.Tensor(11, 5).normal_()\ny = pwl(x)\n\n\nMonotonicity is also supported via `MonoPWL`. See the class documentations for more details.\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "torchpwl", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "torchpwl.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "torchpwl.calibrate1d", "xref": {"fqname": "torchpwl.pwl.calibrate1d", "project": null}}, {"name": "torchpwl.Calibrator", "xref": {"fqname": "torchpwl.pwl.Calibrator", "project": null}}, {"name": "torchpwl.MonoPointPWL", "xref": {"fqname": "torchpwl.pwl.MonoPointPWL", "project": null}}, {"name": "torchpwl.MonoPWL", "xref": {"fqname": "torchpwl.pwl.MonoPWL", "project": null}}, {"name": "torchpwl.PointPWL", "xref": {"fqname": "torchpwl.pwl.PointPWL", "project": null}}, {"name": "torchpwl.PWL", "xref": {"fqname": "torchpwl.pwl.PWL", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl_test", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "torchpwl.pwl_test.max_abs_diff", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "expected", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl_test.get_x", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "num_channels", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "batch_size", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "std", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl_test.test_pwl_init", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pwl_module", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_channels", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_breakpoints", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl_test.test_pwl_default_init_response", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pwl_module", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_channels", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_breakpoints", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl_test.test_pwl_default_init_mono_response", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pwl_module", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_channels", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_breakpoints", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "monotonicity", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl_test.test_pwl_default_init_multi_mono_response", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pwl_module", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_channels", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_breakpoints", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl_test.test_pwl_gradient_flows", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pwl_module", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_channels", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_breakpoints", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl_test.test_pwl_sloped_correct_num_breakpoints", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pwl_module", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_channels", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_breakpoints", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl_test.test_pwl_is_continous", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pwl_module", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_channels", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_breakpoints", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl_test.test_pwl_fits", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pwl_module", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_channels", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_breakpoints", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "optimizer_fn", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl_test.test_input_packing", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pwl_module", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "input_shape", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl_test.test_calibrator_mono_down", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl_test.test_calibrator_mono_up", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl_test.test_calibrator_missing_value", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "torchpwl.pwl_test.TOLERANCE", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "torchpwl.pwl.get_monotonicity", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "monotonicity", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_channels", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.calibrate1d", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "x", "type": {"name": "torch.Tensor", "xref": {"fqname": "torch.Tensor", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "xp", "type": {"name": "torch.Tensor", "xref": {"fqname": "torch.Tensor", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "yp", "type": {"name": "torch.Tensor", "xref": {"fqname": "torch.Tensor", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "torch.Tensor", "xref": {"fqname": "torch.Tensor", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Performs piecewise linear interpolation for x, using xp and yp keypoints (knots).\n\nPerforms separate interpolation for each channel.\n\nArgs:\n\n: x: [N, C] points to be calibrated (interpolated). Batch with C channels.\n  xp: [C, K] x coordinates of the PWL knots. C is the number of channels, K is the number of knots.\n  yp: [C, K] y coordinates of the PWL knots. C is the number of channels, K is the number of knots.\n\nReturns:\n\n: Interpolated points of the shape [N, C].\n\nThe piecewise linear function extends for the whole x axis (the outermost keypoints define the outermost\ninfinite lines).\nFor example:\n\\>>> calibrate1d(torch.tensor(\\[[0.5]\\]), torch.tensor(\\[[0.0, 1.0]\\]), torch.tensor(\\[[0.0, 2.0]\\]))\ntensor(\\[[1.0000]\\])\n\\>>> calibrate1d(torch.tensor(\\[[-10]\\]), torch.tensor(\\[[0.0, 1.0]\\]), torch.tensor(\\[[0.0, 2.0]\\]))\ntensor(\\[[-20.0000]\\])\n"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "torchpwl.pwl.BasePWL", "bases": ["torch.nn.Module"], "methods": [{"name": "torchpwl.pwl.BasePWL.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_breakpoints", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.BasePWL.slope_at", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.Calibrator", "bases": ["torch.nn.Module"], "methods": [{"name": "torchpwl.pwl.Calibrator.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "keypoints", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "monotonicity", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "missing_value", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Calibrates input to the output range of [-0.5*monotonicity, 0.5*monotonicity].\nThe output is always monotonic with respect to the input.\nRecommended to use Adam for training. The calibrator is initalized as a straight line.\n\nvalue <= keypoint[0] will map to -0.5*monotonicity.\nvalue >= keypoint[-1] will map to 0.5*monotonicity.\nvalue == missing_value will map to a learnable value (within the standard output range).\nEach channel is independently calibrated and can have its own keypoints.\nNote: monotonicity and keypoints are not trainable, they remain fixed, only the calibration output at\neach keypoint is trainable.\n\nkeypoints: tensor with shape [C, K], where K > 2\nmonotonicity: tensor with shape [C]\nmissing_value: float"]}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.Calibrator.forward", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Calibrates input x tensor. x has shape [BATCH_SIZE, C]."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.BasePWLX", "bases": ["BasePWL"], "methods": [{"name": "torchpwl.pwl.BasePWLX.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_channels", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_breakpoints", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_x_points", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.BasePWLX._reset_x_points", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.BasePWLX.get_x_positions", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.BasePWLX.get_sorted_x_positions", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.BasePWLX.get_spreads", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.BasePWLX.unpack_input", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.BasePWLX.repack_input", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "unpacked", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "old_shape", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.BasePointPWL", "bases": ["BasePWLX"], "methods": [{"name": "torchpwl.pwl.BasePointPWL.get_y_positions", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.BasePointPWL.forward", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.PointPWL", "bases": ["BasePointPWL"], "methods": [{"name": "torchpwl.pwl.PointPWL.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_channels", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_breakpoints", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.PointPWL._reset_params", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.PointPWL.get_x_positions", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.PointPWL.get_y_positions", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.MonoPointPWL", "bases": ["BasePointPWL"], "methods": [{"name": "torchpwl.pwl.MonoPointPWL.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_channels", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_breakpoints", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "monotonicity", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.MonoPointPWL._reset_params", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.MonoPointPWL.get_x_positions", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.MonoPointPWL.get_y_positions", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.BaseSlopedPWL", "bases": ["BasePWLX"], "methods": [{"name": "torchpwl.pwl.BaseSlopedPWL.get_biases", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.BaseSlopedPWL.get_slopes", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.BaseSlopedPWL.forward", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.PWL", "bases": ["BaseSlopedPWL"], "methods": [{"name": "torchpwl.pwl.PWL.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_channels", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_breakpoints", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.PWL._reset_params", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.PWL.get_biases", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.PWL.get_x_positions", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.PWL.get_slopes", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Piecewise Linear Function (PWL) module.\n\nThe module takes the Tensor of (N, num_channels, ...) shape and returns the processed Tensor of the same shape.\nEach entry in the input tensor is processed by the PWL function. There are num_channels separate PWL functions,\nthe PWL function used depends on the channel.\n\nThe x coordinates of the breakpoints are initialized randomly from the Gaussian with std of 2. You may want to\nuse your own custom initialization depending on the use-case as the optimization is quite sensitive to the\ninitialization of breakpoints. As long as your data is normalized (zero mean, unit variance) the default\ninitialization should be fine.\n\nArguments:\n    num_channels (int): number of channels (or features) that this PWL should process. Each channel\n        will get its own PWL function.\n    num_breakpoints (int): number of PWL breakpoints. Total number of segments constructing the PWL is\n        given by num_breakpoints + 1. This value is shared by all the PWL channels in this module."]}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.MonoPWL", "bases": ["PWL"], "methods": [{"name": "torchpwl.pwl.MonoPWL.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_channels", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_breakpoints", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "monotonicity", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "torchpwl.pwl.MonoPWL.get_slopes", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Piecewise Linear Function (PWL) module with the monotonicity constraint.\n\nThe module takes the Tensor of (N, num_channels, ...) shape and returns the processed Tensor of the same shape.\nEach entry in the input tensor is processed by the PWL function. There are num_channels separate PWL functions,\nthe PWL function used depends on the channel. Each PWL is guaranteed to have the requested monotonicity.\n\nThe x coordinates of the breakpoints are initialized randomly from the Gaussian with std of 2. You may want to\nuse your own custom initialization depending on the use-case as the optimization is quite sensitive to the\ninitialization of breakpoints. As long as your data is normalized (zero mean, unit variance) the default\ninitialization should be fine.\n\nArguments:\n    num_channels (int): number of channels (or features) that this PWL should process. Each channel\n        will get its own PWL function.\n    num_breakpoints (int): number of PWL breakpoints. Total number of segments constructing the PWL is\n        given by num_breakpoints + 1. This value is shared by all the PWL channels in this module.\n    monotonicity (int, Tensor): Monotonicty constraint, the monotonicity can be either +1 (increasing), \n        0 (no constraint) or -1 (decreasing). You can provide either an int to set the constraint \n        for all the channels or a long Tensor of shape [num_channels]. All the entries must be in -1, 0, +1."]}], "exports": []}]}